Cats and dogs and anyone at all, today I want to talk about something near and deer to my heart:

Buttons.....

Buttons are the unsung hero of our world.  They do things!  Like make lights light up, make your bank balance go up and down, make your temporary transportation room go up and down, and even make your bed go up and down!  They make radio waves jiggle in such a way that you can make your friend's pocket computer box display lights in a pattern that resembles a cat.  They make sustenance fall from the glass snack box (and then makes your bank balance go mostly down).

And the coolest thing is all these buttons have one thing you have to do to them:  You poke them!  You poke the button, and all these things could happen.  Think about how hard it would be to have a nice life if you couldn't poke the button.  No wonder I get upset when my partner pokes the temporary transportation room button:  I WANTED TO POKE THE TEMPORARY TRANSPORTATION ROOM BUTTON!  YOU GOT TO LAST TIME!  WH... oh... *cough*, sorry, I swear I'm an adult.

If there's one message I want to send:

Buttons..... Poke `em if ya got `em.

It's Sunday Service time!

Often times, we use this space for quirky and silly things, but I feel moved to say something a little different today:

There's a lot going on right now, and so much of it taxes us.  It's understandable to be angry, or worried.  It's understandable to be scared and overwhelmed.  But I want to shine a little bit of a different light:  What I'm also seeing right now is people caring.  They're refusing to be complacent in that scary space.  People CARE about all of this, and they CARE about YOU.  You deserve to have a space where right and wrong matter.  You deserve to have a space where you are safe and at home.  You deserve to have a space where it's ok to make decisions and boundaries for the sake of ALL of us living together as a human species.  It's scary, yes.  But those people around you who are doing the people we get to live with.  And I think that's a wonderful thing.

Love each other, love yourself, and our world will continue to be a wonderful place.

First, A stroopwafel is a thin, round waffle made from two layers of sweet baked dough held together by syrup filling. First made in the city of Gouda in South Holland, stroopwafels are a well-known Dutch treat popular throughout the Netherlands and abroad.

A stroopwafel's wafer layers are made from a stiff dough of flour, butter, brown sugar, yeast, milk, and eggs that has been pressed in a hot waffle iron until crisp. While still warm, the waffles have their edges removed with a cookie cutter, which allows the remaining disc to be easily separated into top and bottom wafers. A filling made from syrup, brown sugar, butter, and cinnamonâ€”also warmâ€”is spread between the wafers before the waffle is reassembled. ## Happy Anniversary Sunday Service!!!
Four years ago, a group of floofs decided to continue the traditions of a smooth and enjoyable end of one week and start of the next~ Through their dedication, we still celebrate each Sunday with wonderful vibes and good company!

While we may not have any fancy world event or FX for this anniversary event, we gathered up as many of the founders available and today is filled with the vibes that started it all! Weâ€™re also starting an hour earlier than normal to include a few folks that frequent the church!! 

Violet Thunder opens the evening with some melodically organic house. Kittz takes us back to the roots with some funky vibes for 90 minutes, then Strawbs rounds out that hour with some live trumpet vibes! The founder fun continues with Icedog and Whitty taking us to wherever they feel necessary (somewhere great, thatâ€™s for sure~) before we jump into our **debutt** for the night - Pineapple - giving us a cerebral high with a lovely psytrance mix. Dua further melts minds and winds us down with some psychill/downtempo before Bleatr wraps up the celebration of our fourth year. Get ready to vibe, this weekâ€™s definitely smoother than most~

So, whether this is your first or your many-hundreth Sunday Service, welcome in and enjoy connecting with the Infinite Beat!! Remember to love yourself, love one another, and keep the good vibes flowing. Sunday is never the end of a good weekend, itâ€™s simply the transition to the next amazing week ahead~

A special thank you to Strawbs, Kaz, Kittz, Schlick, Whitty, Windy, and Frosty for becoming friends so many years back and forming S4 into the wonderful home it is today! The clubhouse maintains such a unique vibe and fosters so many new DJs into our rave scene. This place is truly life changing and may the next years ahead only grow the love and support already within! :nekoloves:
